investigation.title: Characterization of Biofilm Formation, Growth, and Gene Expression on Different Materials and Environmental Conditions in Microgravity (Gene expression of Pseudomonas aeruginosa biofilms)
investigation.description: Microorganisms' natural ability to live as organized multicellular communities – also known as biofilms – provides them with unique survival advantages. For instance, biofilms are protected against environmental stresses thanks to their extracellular matrix, which could contribute to persistent infections after treatment.

project.funding: This project was supported by the National Aeronautics and Space Administration under Grants No. 80NSSC17K0036 and 80NSSC21K1950.
